Cell["\<\
The commutator relations for the fundamental operators produces curvature \
terms consisting of symmetrizations and BoxCDe. This can be turned into \
curvature spinors by ExpandBoxCDe.
In this example we use the function GiveIndicesToTensor so we don\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]t have to write all indices manually.\
\>", "MathCaption",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.518749805372766*^9, 3.518749875448089*^9}, {
   3.5441001053214297`*^9, 3.544100145725501*^9}, 3.5449509679728975`*^9, 
   3.545113835182695*^9, {3.59212073596671*^9, 3.592120744176722*^9}, {
   3.5921215560888586`*^9, 3.592121605748928*^9}, {3.5921225076201906`*^9, 
   3.5921225667902737`*^9}, {3.5921229554708176`*^9, 3.592123000771881*^9}, {
   3.592126153678295*^9, 3.5921262915784883`*^9}, {3.59212664264998*^9, 
   3.5921267794901714`*^9}, {3.5921268117602167`*^9, 3.59212681422022*^9}, {
   3.5921268622502875`*^9, 3.5921269432904005`*^9}, {3.5921279674918346`*^9, 
   3.592128016321903*^9}, {3.956191700293194*^9, 
