Cell["\<\
To commute operators which are not outermost, we can use \
FunctionInFundSpinOp. Often there will be derivatives of products in an \
intermediate step. These will be expanded with the standard Leibniz rule. \
After that, the function ToFundSpinOp to converts all derivatives to \
fundamental spinor operators.\
\>", "MathCaption",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.518749805372766*^9, 3.518749875448089*^9}, {
   3.5441001053214297`*^9, 3.544100145725501*^9}, 3.5449509679728975`*^9, 
